					<span style="font-size:15px; color:#191919;font-weight:bold; ">HOME OF THE LAKERS: </span><span style="font-size:15px; color:#191919;"> Empowering 21st century learners in a safe and respectful learning environment with reflection, technology, and collaboration. • Be Respectful. • Be Responsible. • Be Safe.</span><span style="font-size:14px; color:#191919;"><br>__________________________________________________________________<br></span><span style="font-size:17px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; ">SENIOR PARENTS </span><span style="font-size:16px; ">Parents of Seniors who are interested in ordering a yard sign to celebrate their son/daughters graduation should contact Anita Pease for information and order forms.</span><span style="font-size:17px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; "><br><br>SUPERINTENDENT UPDATE April  16, 2020 </span><span style="font:17px Calibri; ">READ the latest letter from Mr. Bachmeier. </span><span style="font:17px Calibri; "><a href="Office/downloads-3/index.html" title="Letters Home">Please click here to download the full text on PDF.</a></span><span style="font:16px Calibri; "><a href="Office/downloads-3/index.html" title="Letters Home"><br></a></span><span style="font:16px Calibri; "><br></span><span style="font-size:17px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; ">DISTANCE LEARNING PLAN </span><span style="font-size:15px; ">Approved March 27, 2020, by Governor Doug Burgum and State Superintendent Kirsten Baesler. </span><span style="font-size:15px; "><a href="Office/downloads-3/index.html" title="Letters Home">Click here for a PDF download.</a></span><span style="font-size:13px; "><br></span><span style="font-size:17px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; "><br>INFORMATION FOR DLBHS Students </span><span style="font-size:17px; color:#FB0106;"><a href="https://www.smore.com/najk3" rel="external">Click Here!<br></a></span><span style="font-size:15px; color:#434343;"><br></span><span style="font-size:17px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; ">PLEASE READ: </span><span style="font-size:17px; ">With the Governor’s declaration on Thursday March 19, 2020 we will not be opening our buildings to students until further notice</span><span style="font-size:17px; font-weight:bold; ">. We will begin distance learning as announced last week on Tuesday March 24, 2020.</span><span style="font-size:19px; "> </span><span style="font-size:18px; "><br></span><span style="font-size:18px; "><br></span><span style="font-size:18px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; ">7-12 Grade Parents</span><span style="font-size:18px; "> must read this. Click the link below. <br></span><span style="font-size:18px; color:#084FD1;"><u><a href="https://www.smore.com/n1mpy">https://www.smore.com/n1mpy</a></u></span><span style="font-size:18px; "><br></span><span style="font-size:17px; color:#434343;"><br></span><span style="font-size:15px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; ">Menu</span><span style="font-size:20px; font-weight:bold; "><br></span><span style="font:10px Calibri; "><br></span><span style="font-size:17px; font-weight:bold; ">Monday, April 27<br></span><span style="font-size:17px; ">Breakfast – Cereal, Milk, Juice<br>Lunch – Oriental Chicken, White Rice<br>               Fruit, Salad   <br><br></span><span style="font-size:17px; font-weight:bold; ">Tuesday, April 28<br></span><span style="font-size:17px; ">Breakfast – Muffin , Milk, Juice<br>Lunch – Turkey &amp; Cheese Sandwich<br>               Chips, fresh veg., fruit<br><br></span><span style="font-size:17px; font-weight:bold; ">Wednesday, April 29<br></span><span style="font-size:17px; ">Breakfast – Laker Breakfast<br>Lunch – Chicken Strips, Salad, Fruit   <br><br></span><span style="font-size:17px; font-weight:bold; ">Thursday, April 30<br></span><span style="font-size:17px; ">Breakfast – Breakfast Bar, Milk, Juice<br>Lunch – Pulled Pork on a Bun<br>                Coleslaw, Fries, Fruit<br><br></span><span style="font-size:17px; font-weight:bold; ">Friday, May 1<br></span><span style="font-size:17px; ">Breakfast – Cereal, Milk, Juice<br>Lunch – Hamburger on a Bun<br>               Pork &amp; Beans, Fruit<br><br></span><span style="font-size:17px; font-weight:bold; ">A BIG THANK YOU to TARGET FOR OUR<br></span><span style="font-size:17px; font-weight:bold; ">LUNCH BAGS &amp; MARKETPLACE </span><span style="font-size:16px; "><br></span><span style="font-size:22px; font-weight:bold; "><br></span><br><span style="font-size:15px; color:#434343;"><br></span><span style="font-size:18px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; ">Meals Request Form </span><span style="font-size:18px; color:#000000;">Meals will be delivered on standard school days starting on Monday, March 23. You will receive one breakfast and one lunch per day. Pick will be from 11:00 AM to 1:00 PM. Meals are free to any children ages 1 to 18. </span><span style="font-size:18px; color:#000000;"><em>Please fill out the form each day before by 1:00 PM if you want meals the following day.</em></span><span style="font-size:18px; color:#000000;"> ( Example: If you want food on Monday, fill out the form by Friday before 1:00 PM.) </span><span style="font-size:18px; color:#000000;"><a href="https://fs20.formsite.com/UnitedPublicSchool7/0ixojwcedy/index.html">Click here to fill out a meals request</a></span><span style="font-size:18px; color:#000000;">.</span><span style="font-size:18px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; "><br><br>Covid-19 Letter to Parents </span><span style="font-size:16px; ">Download and read the entire letter from Mr. Bachmeier by </span><span style="font-size:16px; "><a href="Office/downloads-3/index.html" title="Letters Home">clicking here</a></span><span style="font-size:16px; ">.</span><span style="font-size:18px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; "><br><br>Instant Information</span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#FB0106;">. </span><span style="font-size:16px; "> See all of the events and activities at DLB! Sign up for the RSS feed and get updates instantly when changes occur. </span><span style="font-size:16px; "><a href="https://www.rschoolnorthdakota.org/public/genie/1266/school/568/" rel="external">Click here for information and to sign up</a></span><span style="font-size:16px; ">.</span><span style="font-size:16px; "><br></span><span style="font-size:16px; "><br></span><span style="font-size:17px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; ">Farm Credit Services of ND</span><span style="font-size:17px; "> six $1,000 Scholarships for the Minot area. </span><span style="font-size:17px; "><a href="(null)/(null)" title="Counselors Corner">Click here to download and view an informational PDF.</a></span><span style="font-size:17px; "><br></span><span style="font-size:17px; "><br></span><span style="font-size:17px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; ">American Legion Auxiliary Scholarships </span><span style="font-size:17px; ">7 different scholarships. </span><span style="font-size:17px; "><a href="(null)/(null)" title="Counselors Corner">Click here to download and view an informational PDF.</a></span><span style="font-size:17px; "><br></span><span style="font-size:17px; "><br></span><span style="font-size:17px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; ">Kindergarten Pre-Registration.</span><span style="font-size:17px; "> </span><span style="font-size:17px; "><a href="https://fs20.formsite.com/UnitedPublicSchool7/p7bb659lol/index.html">Please click here to register for the 2020-21 school year</a></span><span style="font-size:17px; ">. </span><span style="font-size:16px; "><a href="https://fs20.formsite.com/UnitedPublicSchool7/p7bb659lol/index.html"><br></a></span><span style="font-size:15px; color:#FF0000;font-weight:bold; "><br></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#FF0000;font-weight:bold; ">LAKER SCOOP: SCHOOL NEWS</span><span style="font-size:13px; "><br></span><span style="font-size:14px; "><br></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; "><br>Insights of North Dakota</span><span style="font-size:15px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; "> </span><span style="font-size:14px; color:#191919;">is</span><span style="font-size:17px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; "> </span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#000000;">the state’s official source for information about public education across North Dakota. The information is provided by partner agencies through the Statewide Longitudinal Data System and is brought about through the collaborative work efforts of the following North Dakota agencies: Dept. of Public Instruction, Career and Technical Education, ND University System. </span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#000000;"><a href="https://insights.nd.gov" rel="external">Click here.</a></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; "><br></span><span style="font-size:17px; color:#000000;"><br></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; "><br></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; ">Online Library </span><span style="font-size:16px; "><a href="Office/downloads-5/index.html" title="Schedules/Info">Click here to download a PDF</a></span><span style="font-size:16px; "> with instructions to access Overdrive, an online library available to Laker students. The title of the PDF is "Overdrive Instruction."<br></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; "><a href="Office/downloads-3/index.html" title="Letters Home"><br></a></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; ">2019 -2020 School Calendar </span><span style="font-size:16px; "><a href="Office/downloads-5/index.html" title="Schedules/Info">Click here to download</a></span><span style="font-size:16px; "> a PDF detailing the year's school calendar.</span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; "><br><br>PEANUT FREE</span> <span style="font-size:16px; ">Letter against "tree nut allergies." </span><span style="font-size:16px; "><a href="Office/downloads-3/index.html" rel="external" title="Letters Home">Click here to download and read</a></span><span style="font-size:16px; ">.</span><br><br><span style="font-size:16px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; ">LAKER TIME RESOURCE WEBSITE </span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#000000;">Students follow this link for information dealing with your </span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#000000;"><a href="https://sites.google.com/dlblakers.com/lakertime/home">Laker Time</a></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#000000;"> projects.</span><span style="font:16px Calibri; "><br></span><span style="font-size:14px; color:#191919;"><br></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#FF0000;font-weight:bold; ">HIGH SCHOOL COURSE CATALOG </span><span style="font-size:15px; color:#191919;">Parents and students can</span><span style="font-size:15px; color:#191919;"><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1FsAs78P9ocKt7r9N5706ZZ7bGdjv8VWyjhvbF2Jphdo/edit" rel="external"> click here </a></span><span style="font-size:15px; color:#191919;">to read about our course offerings for the coming 2019-20 school year.<br></span><span style="font-size:14px; color:#191919;"><br></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#FF0000;font-weight:bold; ">NEWSLETTER! DES LACS - BURLINGTON ELEMENTARY </span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#000000;">now has a newsletter. Download, print or read the newsletter by </span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#000000;"><a href="downloads-13/index.html" title="BDL Newsletter">clicking here</a></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#000000;">.<br><br></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#FF0000;font-weight:bold; ">NEWSLETTER! DES LACS - BURLINGTON HIGH SCHOOL </span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#000000;font-weight:bold; "> </span><span style="font-size:15px; color:#000000;"> Each month, we will bring you some of the news from the high school including classroom happenings, announcements about coming events, and extracurricular and co-curricular updates. We will also highlight staff members, students of the month, and more.</span><span style="font-size:15px; color:#000000;"><a href="https://www.smore.com/fh3n6"> </a></span><span style="font-size:15px; color:#000000;"><a href="www.smore.com">Click here.</a></span><span style="font-size:15px; color:#000000;"><br></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#FF0000;font-weight:bold; "><br></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#FB0106;font-weight:bold; ">SCHOLARSHIPS</span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#000000;"> are available. </span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#000000;"><a href="(null)/(null)" title="Counselors Corner">Click here</a></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#000000;"> to go to the Counselor's Corner to see the latest.</span><span style="font-size:14px; "><br></span><span style="font:12px Times, Georgia, Courier, serif; "><br></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#FF0000;font-weight:bold; ">PARENTS LEAD </span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#000000;">This is website that provides tools for parents and professionals on issues that are difficult to address. It also gives you teaching tools to engage in ongoing conversations with children or grandchildren. </span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#000000;"><a href="www.parentslead.org" rel="external">Check it out here</a></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#000000;">.<br><br></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#FF0000;font-weight:bold; ">HOUSE BILL 1389 </span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#000000;">A student's parent may direct direct the school district not to administer their student any state test. For more informational read the PDFs from the Department of Public Instruction. </span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#000000;"><a href="(null)/(null)" title="House Bill 1389">Please click here.</a></span><span style="font-size:17px; color:#191919;font-weight:bold; "><br><br></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#191919;font-weight:bold; ">Read this note from Souris Valley Special Services:</span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#191919;"> The Souris Valley Special Services website was designed to offer straightforward access to useful special education information for parents, educators, school administrators, and the general public. We have been updating our website to ensure it is accessible to individuals with disabilities. We would like to know how the website is or isn't accessible to you. If you would be willing to share your thoughts, we would appreciate it. Please contact me, Alison Dollar at (701) 857-4410 or by email at Alison.Dollar@svssnd.org. Website:</span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#191919;"><a href="http://svssnd.org"> SVSSND.org</a></span><span style="font-size:17px; color:#191919;font-weight:bold; "><a href="http://svssnd.org"><br></a></span><span style="font-size:17px; color:#191919;font-weight:bold; "><br></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#FF0000;font-weight:bold; ">Online Lunch Payments </span><span style="font-size:16px; ">Your mobile optimized website for United Public School District #7, at no additional cost, is now active as of October 4, 2016.  Click the URL below for access:<br></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#0B4CB3;"><u><a href="https://payments.efundsforschools.com/v3/districts/55858/">https://payments.efundsforschools.com/v3/districts/55858/</a></u></span><span style="font-size:16px; color:#0B4CB3;"><u><br><br></u></span><span style="font-size:15px; "><br><br></span><span style="font-size:14px; color:#191919;"><br></span><span style="font:12px Times, Georgia, Courier, serif; "><br><br><br><br><br></span><span style="font-size:14px; "><br></span>
